[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring circe-literal features**\n\nI’m looking into what circe-literal can do, like enabling JSON literals, compile-time parsing, and interpolation with encoders. It seems the existing functionality covers most needs. I’m wondering about features like discarding whitespace between interpolated values and whether it allows dynamic key interpolation using prebuilt strings. It should support object value interpolation via Option[A] but might duplicate values since those are part of circe core encoders. I need to test these top-level dynamic values for better clarity.\n\n**Investigating circe-literal features**\n\nI’m exploring how the `createsTopLevelScalarJsonValues` handles static top-level scalars, while interpolation doesn’t seem to cover top-level cases. I’m considering adding a feature like `interpolatesTopLevelValuesThroughEncoders`. This could involve logic paths within macros to replace placeholders with parsed JSON. \n\nAdditionally, I’m curious about supporting replacements in object keys with multiple interpolations and whether JSON field names can handle string interpolation. I need to determine if something like `json\"\"\"{ \"greeting\": \"Hello $name\" }\"\"\"` is encoded as a string. It seems like circe-literal is flexible in handling substitutions in both key and value positions.\n\n**Analyzing JSON interpolation**\n\nI’m thinking about whether the parser treats \"Hello <placeholder>\" as a normal string, which might mean post-processing won't replace it. This makes me wonder if a feature for \"interpolating into JSON strings\" could be useful. Can the public API support this? I’m considering how Replacement.apply creates placeholders based on the number of string parts. If interpolation sits inside a JSON string, I need to see if the placeholder is embedded correctly. I might need to check the JsonLiteralMacros for clarity on how placeholders are recognized.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_09b3e30095a781a8016a2a9bfa810c819696e1d603a1b415ba\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKpwL22oiX9mvx1y2pWwEPPlDbIumDP6yUyDROkbnxrq6xhQiiHsTa39Hh1xIlbFhT0nWO3CXRqmAZeu1_rxUb2tMsA6TVcHHoGV3fB5XWm-Aa1bCc-3hPXpC_k30GCHgtiIVkNESZs9mMuw--Qu5wPYu-myljwB-h0Fi_Tpyk40tyMlUa_jqTesjp6XHhHmgbbmRCFgpv5FOW-uoYxO5LfoWmwDnXIT7cYH1IR1qicxp73-wOStGkC7cuXmt5xGJKYhXGGiZlQE3_D7KRTXoRinUEWhNNUGtwjlsFgXWydr1JF6Q5cMMikjPAX_DG51rBPiamjfTPkFZ5Tf1JPNeKjNQ-vDo4vd1kzG8bGPiYoWxE4TGqj8GFxMyaYdSTw6j_j1xeCJtpB80UOuS8bFvieeTQ5h5kP5sw3_xwMrTSpHhd9ygvWJx9JydDpZnbC1kaWG_r3-2arClYWSJC0ngqki7RBAZ7lCcDW1MbVzgOYMYslOIUaU83ihj4WnL_CgZ4r2aS8re5U-VLoBK5VLQ8-o94PeBGYB_pS-q5BiX-MkHUcpWm4c6pNled0R1mAwnvIbnUUhNET-adRZEbh8CrkzENlOZ1pZuZ87kAqyROXSCJ-KUmdQo1WFHcAkO5942XMv2s_HGuzxi6TGS-WcwoGLwBtauudkIAB_aQhcxgp7qFw6Om3FiliTW9t-YpKja_7MBQtjwfJ72ZVaTjCPVp9MQlwhr3xVpVB0cZx3EmBFm4tXSbjBZr-GNMRwSQtpzcDNhvxIbSqz-s-eipdeuY_qwNnIH-9qqJgtqyhTPDkCz6-cAwk-LUHOCFt9ZJkPE4AOj8Gr6KJezKK4wSeMznEhpkf7hzuhJI7XzjZHNmwGRxjVhudZQWWDWe6wFnGZR_kxMFUKczB4XBuTh6mJpIF42SoQeia6dHQIGP489x90ANwp5ViwfAKWl947Vdf9ETwF4iR0HvqPUgYaBVgsUVBy8AwLSMbxtMFKmp_y4wBtO82e9SYHQlbARMxnIEOfEYa5OMROfnjwDB0R8rrWiLsHMOCJxI0DV8eqj6qBmhZIF-c-6IgcZWiZ0LbtVn2Uo-ePXkDjrNzh9weNmktXbifcUQlF3NH0nXnCeA32zihVhI-BRsi7Z5c1WnFhlPAIyMxyTLon1wrFzDeNGYNrm3YXuZ1nlhIJ8-i5zkr1-z2iSYvtQt9OSS33ZzKbVV5OA2u28q7DlkUwxt9FTgbW_ACIo4tOocI4-g3u6kf6HnaIFwCBLlHM9hgtRlf2HsQbUTM7yFHYAvoB1pntkBaLvbjYD98NKJpcdcWjABz8pyj0pL7f6CXcVzdjWgnXd2CVthgj749zFeSP8sBtniIHCYriRWDH9W8lGDxOcFUBD8FXkOpeAESbXr_f-Olr_4uuV68t8QLlj9kfZvaryC0IlyoJ-NQVCfaGnkXSZ5xxsCs883PSJaSe-48gpxdNtAyT87Urnv-BFbXULF5XUcRpVnic6iZ_j1IN07YBG1qpKrFaOz6JIruIzU0a1wHzndexgtR8jgALBmcgcspgYrDVl6PkAToUqIUO-y9-uubtrvZN1Rrt3MB9TsNz-_ADC2UrWfPkGKmU7qQYI4f52Xta4y_roYqNQkO72Xk69k0Wsmorz7xOTYYQi0CtYqVfd7Y9mix-N9ptmIQGtvK__o0bF-53UjVmw9wiWw9XTEa2J2Ebd4TA2g4bml9DkAzisEfJJ2XGBzYi7z2YweY4gg-NzQzx9GibtHS4jSgFv1t4qf5y3WTQUlin8Cx2pkqoqzMUKqLe6nMVoLjHqSUew6ELwRiDMgO3r4